---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const EFFECTIVE_DATE = "March 5, 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use — ShelfSkin"
  description="Terms that govern your access to and use of ShelfSkin: Scan & Track Skincare."
  active="terms"
>
  <header class="policy-header">
    <span class="badge">Effective Date: {EFFECTIVE_DATE}</span>
    <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
    <p>
      These Terms of Use ("Terms") govern your access to and use of the
      ShelfSkin mobile application and related websites (collectively, the
      "Service"), operated by AOHSTD ("we", "our", or "us"). By accessing or
      using the Service, you agree to be bound by these Terms.
    </p>
  </header>

  <!-- ─── IMPORTANT NOTICE ─── -->
  <div class="note" style="margin-top: 18px;">
    <strong>Important:</strong> ShelfSkin is not a medical application. The
    Service is powered by artificial intelligence and provides general skincare
    information for educational purposes only. It is not medical advice, and
    results are not guaranteed to be accurate or complete. Always consult a
    qualified dermatologist or healthcare provider for specific skin concerns.
    See <a href="#disclaimer" style="color: #7C2D12; font-weight: 700;">Section 8</a> for full details.
  </div>

  <!-- ─── 1. ACCEPTANCE ─── -->
  <div class="section" id="acceptance">
    <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        If you do not agree to these Terms, do not use the Service. You agree to
        comply with all applicable laws, regulations, and platform rules
        (including Google Play and Apple App Store policies).
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── 2. ELIGIBILITY ─── -->
  <div class="section" id="eligibility">
    <h2>2. Eligibility</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        You must be at least 13 years of age (or the equivalent minimum age in
        your jurisdiction) to use the Service. If you are under 18, you
        represent that you have your parent's or legal guardian's permission to
        use the Service.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── 3. DESCRIPTION OF SERVICE ─── -->
  <div class="section" id="description">
    <h2>3. Description of the Service</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        ShelfSkin is a skincare product management tool that allows you to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Scan product ingredient lists using your device camera</li>
        <li>Build and manage a digital shelf of your skincare products</li>
        <li>Detect potential ingredient conflicts and synergies between products</li>
        <li>Track product expiry dates and receive reminders</li>
        <li>Receive personalized skincare tips based on your profile and products</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Product scanning uses a third-party AI service (Anthropic) to identify
        ingredients from product labels. Accuracy of scan results depends on
        image quality, label legibility, and product database coverage.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── 4. USE OF SERVICE ─── -->
  <div class="section" id="license">
    <h2>4. Use of the Service</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        Subject to these Terms, we grant you a limited, non-exclusive,
        non-transferable, revocable license to access and use the Service for
        personal, non-commercial purposes.
      </p>
      <p>You agree not to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Misuse the Service or interfere with its normal operation</li>
        <li>Attempt to reverse engineer, decompile, or bypass security measures</li>
        <li>Use the Service to violate laws or third-party rights</li>
        <li>Submit intentionally false or misleading content</li>
        <li>Use automated tools (bots, scrapers) to access the Service</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── 5. SUBSCRIPTIONS ─── -->
  <div class="section" id="billing">
    <h2>5. Subscriptions and Billing</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        ShelfSkin offers a free tier with limited features and an optional
        premium subscription ("ShelfSkin Pro") with additional features such as
        unlimited scans, full conflict and synergy detection, expiry tracking,
        and personalized insights.
      </p>
      <p>
        Billing is processed entirely by the platform provider (Google Play or
        Apple App Store). Subscription details — including price, billing cycle,
        renewal, and cancellation — are presented at the time of purchase and
        are governed by the platform provider's terms.
      </p>
      <p>
        Subscriptions automatically renew unless cancelled before the end of
        the current billing period through the platform provider's subscription
        management settings.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── 6. USER CONTENT ─── -->
  <div class="section" id="content">
    <h2>6. User Content</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        You may submit content to the Service, including product images for
        scanning, product data, and profile information ("User Content"). You
        retain ownership of your User Content.
      </p>
      <p>
        You grant us a limited license to process, transmit, and temporarily
        store User Content solely for the purpose of providing the Service
        (for example, sending a product image to our AI provider for ingredient
        recognition and returning the result to you).
      </p>
      <p>
        You represent that you have all necessary rights to submit User Content
        and that it does not infringe any third-party rights or applicable laws.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── 7. THIRD PARTY SERVICES ─── -->
  <div class="section" id="thirdparty">
    <h2>7. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        The Service relies on the following third-party services:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <b>Anthropic</b> — for AI-powered ingredient recognition from
          scanned product images.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Google Firebase</b> — for analytics, crash reporting, and
          diagnostics.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Google Play / Apple App Store</b> — for app distribution, billing,
          and subscription management.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We are not responsible for third-party services outside of our control.
        Your use of such services may be subject to their separate terms and
        privacy policies.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── 8. SKINCARE DISCLAIMER ─── -->
  <div class="section" id="disclaimer">
    <h2>8. Skincare Information Disclaimer</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        <b>ShelfSkin is not a medical application. It is not intended to
        diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease or skin condition.</b>
      </p>
      <p>
        The Service is powered by artificial intelligence and provides general
        skincare information for educational purposes only. It is not a
        substitute for professional dermatological consultation.
      </p>
      <p>
        Specifically:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <b>AI-generated results:</b> Ingredient detection, conflict analysis,
          synergy identification, and personalized tips are generated using
          artificial intelligence. AI systems can make errors. We do not
          guarantee the accuracy, completeness, or reliability of any
          AI-generated output.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Not medical advice:</b> Phrases such as "may irritate," "consider
          separating," or "best used separately" reflect general skincare best
          practices and are not diagnoses, prescriptions, or medical directives.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Scan accuracy:</b> Scan results depend on image quality, label
          legibility, and AI model capability. We do not guarantee that every
          ingredient will be correctly identified or that all conflicts will
          be detected.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Individual variation:</b> Ingredient interactions may vary by
          product formulation, concentration, individual skin sensitivity,
          region, and product reformulations. What applies generally may not
          apply to your specific situation.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Expiry estimates:</b> Expiry tracking is based on dates you enter
          or general Period After Opening (PAO) estimates. Actual product shelf
          life may vary by storage conditions and formulation.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>No outcome guarantee:</b> We make no representations or warranties
          that following any information, tip, or recommendation provided by
          ShelfSkin will produce any particular skincare result or prevent any
          adverse reaction.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        <b>Always consult a qualified dermatologist or healthcare provider for
        skin concerns, allergies, or adverse reactions.</b>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── 9. DISCLAIMERS (LEGAL) ─── -->
  <div class="section" id="warranty">
    <h2>9. Warranty Disclaimer</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        The Service is provided "as is" and "as available", without warranties
        of any kind, whether express, implied, or statutory, to the maximum
        extent permitted by law.
      </p>
      <p>
        We do not warrant that:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>The Service will be uninterrupted, error-free, or secure</li>
        <li>AI-generated scan results or ingredient detection will be complete or accurate</li>
        <li>Conflict, synergy, or other AI-generated analysis will apply to your specific situation</li>
        <li>Tips or recommendations will produce any particular skincare outcome</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── 10. LIABILITY ─── -->
  <div class="section" id="liability">
    <h2>10. Limitation of Liability</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by law, AOHSTD will not be liable for
        any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages,
        or any loss of profits or revenues, whether incurred directly or
        indirectly, or any loss of data, use, goodwill, or other intangible
        losses, resulting from:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your access to or use of (or inability to access or use) the Service</li>
        <li>Any inaccuracy, error, or omission in AI-generated scan results, conflict detection, synergy identification, or recommendations</li>
        <li>Any skin reaction, irritation, or adverse effect resulting from following information provided by the Service</li>
        <li>Any decision made or action taken based on information provided by the Service</li>
        <li>Any conduct or content of any third party</li>
        <li>Unauthorized access, use, or alteration of your data</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── 11. IP ─── -->
  <div class="section" id="ip">
    <h2>11. Intellectual Property</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        The Service (including software, design, text, graphics, icons, and
        branding) is owned by AOHSTD or its licensors and is protected by
        intellectual property laws. These Terms do not grant you any rights to
        use AOHSTD or ShelfSkin trademarks, logos, or branding without prior
        written permission.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── 12. TERMINATION ─── -->
  <div class="section" id="termination">
    <h2>12. Termination</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        We may suspend or terminate access to the Service at any time if we
        reasonably believe you have violated these Terms, or if required to
        comply with law or protect the Service.
      </p>
      <p>
        You may stop using the Service at any time. You can delete all your
        data through <span class="kbd">Profile → Delete All Data</span>.
        Sections that by their nature should survive termination (including
        disclaimers and limitation of liability) will survive.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── 13. CHANGES ─── -->
  <div class="section" id="changes">
    <h2>13. Changes to These Terms</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        We may update these Terms from time to time. The updated version will
        be indicated by the revised Effective Date above. Continued use of the
        Service after changes become effective constitutes acceptance of the
        updated Terms.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── 14. LAW ─── -->
  <div class="section" id="law">
    <h2>14. Governing Law</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        These Terms are governed by applicable laws. Where required, mandatory
        consumer protection laws in your jurisdiction may apply and prevail.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── 15. CONTACT ─── -->
  <div class="section" id="contact">
    <h2>15. Contact</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        Questions about these Terms? Contact
        <a class="link" href="mailto:support@aohstd.com">support@aohstd.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <footer class="footer">
    <div class="links">
      <a href="/shelfskin">ShelfSkin</a>
      <a href="/shelfskin/privacy">Privacy</a>
      <a href="/terms">AOHSTD Terms</a>
      <a href="mailto:support@aohstd.com">support@aohstd.com</a>
    </div>
    <small>© {new Date().getFullYear()} AOHSTD</small>
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>
